 (You show her the Reins of the Sun Chariot)
 
 We''re looking for information on this, or similar technology.', 0, 1);























 Disgruntled Refugee: I''m still not convinced we haven''t traded one set of invaders for another. If you ask me, the Tollan people shouldn''t be dealing with these Op-CORE types. What have we gotten from this?
 Hasek: Well, we''ve had more food deliveries, recently.
 Disgruntled Refugee: Look kid, food''s only given to people who are loyal to your mother. Mariam''s loyal to Travell and Travell would have us be the lapdogs for these Op-CORE types. I don''t think the Tollan people should be giving over their independence, even for a hot meal. Okay, it''s getting late. Let''s meet again tomorrow.
 
 ', 0, 0);











 ', 0, 0);








 
 
 ', 0, 0);




 
 (You show him the Reins of the Sun Chariot)', 0, 3);




































 
 (He holds up a gleaming crystal object)
 
 This is a Scarab of Ra. Very rare. I can attach it to any device that uses his technology and I can learn about that device. I do not know how or why it works, but it does. Once my slave problems are in the past, I will let you use it.', 399, 4);































































 
 (You show him the Reins of the Sun Chariot)
 
 Specifically information about that.', 0, 5);














































 
 (The transmission is broken up by the pop-pop-pop of live gunfire. Rameris is under attack.)
 
 Kaplan''s troops are right outside... are dead... need relief... 
 
 (The transmission goes dead.)', 212, 0);


























































































 ', 409, 0);




























 
 (He takes a step back)
 
 Get the device!', 534, 4);




































































































































































































































































 
 One of OpCORE''s top spec ops guy, Sgt. Velarde, is already on Anima Vitrus. He''ll point you in the right direction.', 0, 0);


 ', 0, 1);



 
 Geier knows his place here. Learn yours. ', 0, 0);

 
 For example, she says quite the market here for weapons and armor... but those things don''t exactly grow on trees. If you can bring me a some Photon Absorption Fiber, I''ll do a little listening for you. Maybe find this Venio you''re looking for. 
 ', 0, 0);



 
 They''ve got a camp to the south, Camp Frasier. I''ve marked a few key locations on this map. If they have this Venio, they''ll be keeping it at one of those points.', 0, 0);






 
 ', 0, 0);




 
 Talk to Kiel, in the hut to the north. He knows about it personally.', 0, 0);



 
 Find her. Find the doctor.', 0, 0);



 
 I''ll pay you to kill Nichols, and bring me a few of those Ba''taur warbeads while you''re at it. Make me... I mean, us... make us look like war heroes to the Sha.', 0, 0);




 
 A poacher named Willis runs the place. He knows things that no one else has even heard of. It''s almost like he has access to the planet itself. If anyone can provide you with the information you seek, it''s Willis.', 0, 0);

 
 A nearby Tech Con ship crash is crawling with Twilla. Clear ''em out. Our man Kenders will tell ya'' when to stop. 
 
 Oh, and a poaching party left here a few hours ago. They ought to be dead by now. Recover their gear, and I''ll introduce you to our secret weapon, our crystal ball so-to-speak.', 0, 0);








 
 I''ll see that it gets back to the Prim Ha''tak.', 0, 0);



 
 My man Willis in Enderweldt says you''ll be interested in talking with Amaari. The kid''s been asking for you directly.', 0, 0);







































































 
 Find these Ba''taur. Find the Venio, and kill Wertz... if the Ba''taur haven''t killed him already. 
 
 And if they have... you find a way to kill him again. ', 0, 0);

 
 Why not stay here in Sha''drown, where things are good?', 0, 0);

 
 The Ba''taur have corrupted your people. They have used your Colonel Wertz to steal the Venio, and they will use you until the world itself is dead! ', 0, 0);



 
 Velarde will want to see these files. ', 0, 0);

 
 Don''t worry, there''s plenty to be done in the meantime.', 0, 0);


 
 But what they have to do with the Venio? Your guess is as good as mine.', 0, 0);

 
 Investigate the other pods, and uncover the secrets they hold.', 0, 0);



 
 I''ll run it through the computers.', 0, 0);


 
 Amaari, he can hear Anima. Bring the Venio to him and he will listen for you.', 0, 0);

 
 Are you sure you want this? 
 
 Are you sure you want this for the right reasons?', 0, 0);

 
 Take it to Jalleh, a shaman in Sha''las. You will have to pass through Necavi Canyon to get there, but she will tell you what to do next.', 0, 0);

 
 You must take the Venio to the Sermobis, where Straegis gather now. You must take the Venio to Anima.', 0, 0);


 
 One appears to be to the south, near a large lake and a massive ancient structure. The second is inside what appears to be an Ancient lab complex to the west of Sha''las. The third... The third appears to be on the move. It''s like a mountain of these things is walking around. 
 
 Scan these three locations and report back to me immediately.', 0, 0);






 
 We have to find where that gate leads, or things are going to get real ugly real fast.
 
 You''ll have to weaken one of the Straegis before the device will attach, but once it does, it will carry the device through the gate and show us the way.', 0, 0);

 
 Wherever that gate leads, its not in this system. It''s not in this galaxy. It''s not even in this universe. 
 
 It''s just... gone.', 0, 0);



 
 You must find a child who can speak to Anima, a child who can use the Venio. You must find a child who trusts you. ', 0, 0);





 
 Fine. I''ll walk you through it. Tell me what you see...', 0, 0);

 
 ', 0, 1);

 
 Find a UIM and you''re golden.', 0, 2);



 
 Bring me a couple of those fragmentation grenades I''ve seen your people carry, and I''ll get you access to my more eclectic merchandise. 
 
 Deal?
 ', 0, 0);



 
 They sell Gauss Flachette Rifles on almost every rock except this one. Bring me the rifle, a new one, and I will make it worth your while. Is that so hard to understand?
 ', 0, 0);



 
 If you find them and let me know where they went, I will not only let you come along, I will even think about giving you a part of the profits.', 0, 0);




 
 If your friends are wearing those necklaces, then they are not your friends. They are Ba''taur now.', 0, 0);




 
 Please. You have to get me out of here.', 0, 0);



 
 Deliver them to Agent Kurr in Sha''drown.', 0, 0);

 
 Now, go back to Corgan and tell him you want nothing to do with Tech Con here. ', 0, 0);

 
 You seem to be a bit more reliable that Agent Kurr and his men. Perhaps we could come to some sort of cooperative agreement?', 0, 0);






 
 Find my notes, take them... take them to anyone who can use them.', 0, 0);



 
 We sent a squad of contractors in there three days ago to clear the place out so we can get back to work, but they''ve been on radio silence ever since. I''ll pay you out of my own pocket to find out what''s taking so long. ', 0, 0);




 
 Go down to the mines, slice-and-dice a couple of cabages, and I''ll make it worth your while. ', 0, 0);



 
 Head back to the mines and bring me a couple and I''ll show you what we can do with them.', 0, 0);

 
 Here. This is just one example of what we can do with ''em.', 0, 0);






 
 You must travel into Nacavi Canyon. Seek out the weapons they have stored there. Destroy them, or all of Anima will be destroyed.', 0, 0);






 
 (She takes your picture.)
 
 Wait, don''t smile. 
 
 (Another picture.)
 
 Very nice - you''re wonderfully photogenic, did you know that? Bone structure I think. Anyway, add a bit of adhesive, press and... Viola! Here are your credentials, Zohar. ', 156, 0);






































































































 
 I''ll get these back to the SGC so Dr. Jackson can take a look at them.', 0, 0);































 
 We''ll make sure he''s remembered for the good he did over the last few years, not the evil he did in his last few days.', 0, 0);



































 
 We absolutely cannot allow that information to fall into enemy hands. ', 0, 0);








 
 The guardians of the Venio are at war with the outsiders. I regret I cannot help you. I do not wish to cause any more anger. Anima is already in enough pain.
 ', 0, 0);






 
 Geier''s my boss. Best poacher in the wilds of Anima. He practically runs this planet. 
 
 He may be able to help you out... maybe. For a price.', 0, 0);































 
 There has to be someone around here who knows what happened.', 0, 0);

 ', 448, 0);



































 
 You? Talk to those Sha? Not gonna happen. They''ve been on the war path. They love blood. Acquired taste, that.', 0, 0);

















 
 Now, thanks to you guys, the whole thing is slipping through my fingers. A bomb went off in a nearby village, and the Sha are saying the SGC did it. 
 
 Now they won''t even deal with us! ', 0, 0);
































 
 Not that anything makes sense on this world.', 0, 0);



 
 Search Camp Frasier and find his status.', 0, 0);





















 
 Nearly every mission in his files references the device. Venio this, Venio that. It must be the key to the Furling he was looking for. Chief Zanal may have some insight. Talk to him.', 0, 0);








 
 Pretty sick if you ask me.', 0, 0);

 
 I''m the one who showed Wertz which children had the Ancient gene. Do you see?
 
 I didn''t mean to... I didn''t know... I should have known...', 0, 0);


 
 Do what ever it takes to find Wertz and stop him. That''s an order.', 0, 0);


 
 Well, chances are he''s gone beyond the end of the world: Enderweldt. Not for the faint of heart.
 
 I know a guy there. Willis. He can help you out.', 0, 0);

















 
 Let me be your inside contact. Get me a radio from the Ba''taur, and I''ll report back to you with updates.', 0, 0);




 
 We''ve got someone you should talk to. Amaari. The Great Amaari.', 0, 0);


 
 She doesn''t trust you. 
 
 She is afraid.', 0, 1);

 
 Three different groups of people, your people.
 
 I see burning, screaming everywhere... a crash! And a survivor.
 
 I see poachers in the wilderness.
 
 I see an archaeologist. He''s at the Ruins of Shanti. Frightened, so frightened.', 0, 2);

 
 Burtonol''s brute force attacks aren''t working against the Twilla, and they''re going overboard... those psychopaths will kill you if you try to go in there.', 0, 0);



 
 She is silent. Anima is suddenly quiet.
 
 Trouble is brewing.', 0, 0);




 
 The log provides us with the location of the MALP as well as the MALP Encryption Key that will allow data access.', 0, 0);

 
 The last address dialed leads to an unknown location.', 0, 0);

 
 It came up with an active Stargate: the planet known as Vokos Primar.', 0, 0);




 
 No!
 
 She is in pain!
 
 Sha''hawt is holy ground, where Anima is extremely sensitive. You must help her!', 0, 0);


 
 We shall defeat the evil together.
 
 I will rally the Sha for our assault.', 0, 0);


 
 As for the Venio. To revive it, you will need the help of a child. A child who can hear the planet. 
 
 Go to my son.', 0, 0);



 
 But you must identify its nature.', 0, 0);

 
 The Sermobis is Anima''s heart. There, she listens. In her heart.
 
 That is where you will use the Venio.
 
 Jalleh will help you now. Go to Sha''las.', 0, 0);

 
 Only the Straegis enter the Meridian Gate now. Anima, our sacred planet, will decide if you can enter.', 0, 0);


 
 Well, that confirms the activity our remote sensors picked up. Investigate their presence. Measure the levels of Straegis activity at three locations: the Sermobis, the Ancient Lab, and this third coordinate on your map.', 0, 0);




 
 In order to assess the danger of these Straegis Titans, I''m going to need one of their ''theme'' crystals. Unfortunately, the only way to get one is to kill a Titan. It''s going to be rough, but you can do it. You like it rough.', 0, 0);




 
 We need to figure out where the Straegis are going.
 
 That''s right. You''re going to follow that Straegis. ', 0, 0);

 
 Tracking a Straegis will disorient it enough to stop fighting and return to its task.', 0, 1);

 
 How will we stop them from assembling?', 0, 0);

















 
 Does she listen? Yes. She listens to children.', 0, 0);

 
 But I cannot talk to her.
 
 I am a child that is seen, but not heard, by my mother planet.
 ', 0, 0);



 
 Someone older than my people, yet younger than me.
 
 I see in your eyes that you have the answer.', 0, 0);

 
 I can do it.
 
 I want to save the world, too.
 
 Grandpa, can I go?', 0, 0);



 
 I''m tired.
 
 I''m scared!
 
 When will we get there?', 0, 0);

 
 My friend wanted me to talk to you. It''s very important. Is that okay?
 
 The Straegis... what''s that word?... con...convergence. It will destroy us all. Even you.
 
 Can you save us?
 
 Please let my friend use the gate. I''ll stay with you for a little bit, if you want. I know you''re scared too. ', 0, 0);

















