 Hasek: Hello.
 Tollan man: Hasek.
 Tollan Woman: Hey, kid.
 Tollan Man: Hasek''s a smart guy. He''ll agree with me.
 Hasek: Agree with you on what?"
 Tollan Man: We can''t keep letting invaders in. We have to stand up for ourselves. Have some pride! We''ve survived the destruction of our home twice in a decade. We''re survivors and need to act like it and be strong.
 Hasek: Well.
 Tollan Woman: There is nothing wrong with forming alliances. We''re not going to get the Goa''uld to go away with guerilla tactics and a few home-made pipe bombs.
 Hasek: I think-
 Tollan man: These Op-CORE types aren''t much better than the Goa''uld. I don''t want to trade one overlord for another.
 Hasek: I''ll see you around', 0, 0);





 Tollan man 1: Well, I''ve lost faith in Travell, I don''t see- Oh. Hello Hasek.
 Tollan Man 2: Hey Hasek.
 Hasek: Hello.
 Man 2: She''s not the only one to blame in this. I''m not sure I care for Narim either.
 Man 1: Narim wouldn''t have been in the position he was in if it hadn''t been for Travell and the Curia. You can''t tell me you don''t want to see them stop their power plays.
 Man 2: Well, no. But I''m not sure I agree with Narim''s politics either.
 Hasek: The Rebels have blown up some things. The Goa''uld don''t like that too much.
 Man 2: See? That''s what I''m talking about. Violence isn''t the answer. I''m not sure I can agree with Narim''s tactics.
 Man 1: We''re all thinking the same thing. Narim''s just the only person who''s had enough guts to say it out loud. The Goa''uld don''t understand anything but force. Now, I could get behind the Curia if they were more willing to stand up to the Goa''uld. Why don''t you have your mother tell her mistress that Hasek?
 Man 2: That''s a bit harsh Clasan. Come on, let''s go. I''ll see you around Hasek.', 0, 0);

 Tollan Teen: Hi Hasek!
 Tollan Adult: Hasek.
 Hasek: Hey. How are you doing?
 Teen: I''m okay. My mom''s worried about my brother, Davan, so she''s not really letting me go anywhere.
 Adult: I''m sure he''s just fine, Javry.
 Hasek: Where''d he go? I just saw him the other day.
 Teen: He joined the Rebels.
 Hasek: That''s kind of dangerous isn''t it?
 Adult: Narim''s taking good care of his people. He''s a good man.
 Teen: I think so. Mom''s not so convinced. I got one of the recordings but she took it.
 Adult: Well, I''ve heard the Rebels have someone available over on the western side of the settlement. Maybe you could get a message to your brother and another copy of the recordings.
 Teen: That''s a good idea. Mom might not be so annoying if she knows Davan''s ok.
 Adult: You should go hear what they have to say too, Hasek. They make a lot of good points.
 Hasek: [shrug] Maybe. I''ll see you later, bye!', 0, 0);

 Rebel 1: This sends a decisive message. We don''t want them here.
 Rebel 2: You sure? Blowing up their main base is a bit harsh. They haven''t really done anything to us yet.
 Rebel 1: and now they''ll think twice about it.', 0, 0);




 
